      <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-6">
    		<h2>About the Curator</h2>
        <p>Hi, I'm <a href="http://alannarisse.com" target="_blank">Alanna Risse</a>. I live in two worlds. I have been both and artist and a web developer for most of my adult life. I've always been curious at the interesection between these two worlds. I've worked at a few tech companies with fantastic contemporary art collections and I love watching self proclaimed non-artists develop relationships with art in their workplace.</p>
        <p>Art galleries and museums can be intimidating for people who don't consider themselves to be "artists." I think office spaces can offer a really rich opportunity to develop a love of art. When you can see the same works of art day after day, you get a much richer experience than if you spend 5 minutes (or less) looking at something in a gallery or museum. For me, this is where artworks can be transformed into something meaningful and powerful. I want to bring great art into spaces where people can experience it.</p>
